{
  "stem": "23438.2",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "I mean, with all that poverty, and lack of food in the ghetto, there were still fresh bread rolls every morning, which is quite amazing.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "I don't know how much money we'd made on that.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "I know that I was continuously hungry and I would, every day, eat one or two rolls on the way and tell my mother that the baker had made a mistake, that he'd [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "My mother was making some additional money-- as I found out one day being nosy a little bit-- by selling contraceptives among her friends.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] It wasn't easy.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "We'd buy-- we'd get a ration of bread for four people.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And we had to cut it into four pieces amongst my grandmother, my uncle, and the two of us.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they were all looking, whose piece is just a little bit bigger than the other one?",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We'd get two potatoes.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And we had to cook them and-- and divide them into four servings.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] A lot of the food was, come winter, frozen and hardly possible to eat, like frozen potatoes, frozen pumpkin.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That was quite a monstrosity.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] On the other hand, there were some reasonably good times.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "School, as I said, was strictly forbidden, under death sentence.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But there were, underground, illegal schools operating throughout Warsaw.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And the same in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And there I went to a school called [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "That was originally, before the war, a boys-only school.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But in the ghetto, they-- they had girls' groups and boys' groups.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We had groups of no more than five or six meeting in private flats.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "There were six girls in the group I went to.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Out of them, I know one only, besides myself, that survived.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
